 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 509674348.0, 'datetime': '2019-07-09 14:49:37+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "@username_7 I don't own the official instance, so nobody can fix this except the author.  You may try using an alternative instance (i.e. anything that's NOT official), like @staticmanlab, @staticmanaima, @BloggerBust-bot, etc.

P.S. I maintain the first one, and I helped the setup of the 2nd one through GitHub issues.  I've only tested mine.  If you want to use mine, please refer to the later half of https://github.com/einsteinpy/blog.einsteinpy.org/issues/12#issue-449871630 and adapt it to your repo.  I'm too lazy to retype everything again.  Please don't hesitate to ping me in case of questions.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'zxdawn2', 'comment_id': 510276267.0, 'datetime': '2019-07-11 00:12:14+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_7', 'text': '@username_6 I tried to visit `https://staticman3.herokuapp.com/v3/connect/github/username_7/username_7.github.io/master/comments`, but I get this error:
```
Cannot GET /v3/connect/github/username_7/username_7.github.io/master/comments
```

BTW,  I use this method to add comments:
```
<form method="POST" action="https://staticman3.herokuapp.com/v3/connect/github/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.username }}/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.repository }}/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.branch }}/comments">
```

As a result, when I try to post, I got this error:
```
Cannot POST /v3/connect/github/username_7/username_7.github.io/master/comments
```', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 510478125.0, 'datetime': '2019-07-11 13:08:50+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': '@username_7 Thanks for your invitation to @staticmanlab.

1. The link for accepting the invitation is  
https://staticman3.herokuapp.com/v3/connect/github/username_7/username_7.github.io/  
Explanation: You invite a GitHub/GitLab user to the *whole* repo, not just to a particular branch.
2. To hook up your HTML form with Staticman API. you need `/entry` instead of `/connect`.

       <form method="POST" action="https://staticman3.herokuapp.com/v3/entry/github/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.username }}/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.repository }}/{{ .Site.Params.staticman.branch }}/comments">

    Note that `comments` is just a property name in `staticman.yml`.  You may change it to any name you like.  For example, https://github.com/okfde/offenerhaushalt.de/blob/gh-pages/staticman.yml.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'zxdawn2', 'comment_id': 517895169.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-03 05:09:02+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_7', 'text': "@username_6 thanks!
Although comment works, subscribe button doesn't work:
https://github.com/username_7/username_7.github.io/blob/3a9b470ddd13ac1c8bb2831d1e15d30d55505ef2/themes/AllinOne/layouts/partials/staticman/form-comments.html#L30-L37
Is that caused by @staticmanlab?", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 517897763.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-03 06:00:25+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "@staticmanlab _doesn't_ touch Akismet and Mailgun because his main goal is to show that Staticman's GitLab integration works, so that a truly open-source staticman commenting system is, in principle, feasible, for static sites hosted on Framagit, which is open-source.

Before the appearance of a free (as in both free beer and in freedom) alternative of Akismet and/or Mailgun, @staticmanlab won't try them.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'zxdawn2', 'comment_id': 517933796.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-03 15:40:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_7', 'text': 'Thanks! However, mailgun has free account option. Why not support it?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 517934771.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-03 15:55:11+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': '1. In this case, "free" as in "free beer" is offered, but not "free" as in "freedom" in GNU's norms.
2. @staticmanlab's main goal is to test and demonstrate Staticman's native GitLab support, which had not yet been merged against the `master` branch, so I tried my best to minimise the [setup](https://vincenttam.gitlab.io/post/2018-09-16-staticman-powered-gitlab-pages/2/) and the corresponding [git diff between the `dev` branch at `55d14306` and my `deploy` branch](https://github.com/eduardoboucas/staticman/compare/55d14306d851059a2a27d24b5eb4cb17c5009477..username_6:deploy).', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'zxdawn2', 'comment_id': 522232156.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-17 12:21:18+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_7', 'text': '@username_6 Thank you for your help! I rebuilded the [repository](https://github.com/username_7/username_7.github.io) and got another problem:
The Comment content at the end of this [page](https://username_7.github.io/2019/08/17/hugo-staticman-travis/#/reference) looks different from local (hugo server).

Local: 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50947063/63211626-63499800-c12c-11e9-9e0c-a4c8d620fdca.png)

WEB:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50947063/63211629-70ff1d80-c12c-11e9-8c30-9716c7af9fbd.png)', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 522233308.0, 'datetime': '2019-08-17 12:40:24+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': '1. The project is about the Node.JS app that converts HTML form data into GitHub/GitLab pull/merge requests.  It *shouldn't* care whether you use GitHub/GitLab pages or not, as @<span></span>eduardoboucas commented in https://github.com/eduardoboucas/staticman/issues/278#issuecomment-475170669.  Your project is about the display of a HTML form, which has *nothing* to do with the structure of the form data, so perhaps you have to find a better place to ask, like [Hugo Discourse](https://discourse.gohugo.io/).
2. To ensure that your Staticman config is correct, a quick way to test is to use API clients like [Postman](https://www.getpostman.com/), as @<span></span>ntsim suggested in #219.
3. Please be aware of the "503 Service Unavailable" error of the official production instance "api.staticman.net".', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
